casebody.data:
Lindsey Joy HANSON, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Anne Lorraine MAIRE; New Orleans City, Defendants-Appellees. No. 07-30860. United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 6, 2008. James E. Uschold, New Orleans, LA, for Plaintiff-Appellant. Michael R. Sistrunk, McCranie Sistrunk Anzelmo Hardy Maxwell & McDaniel, Me-tairie, LA, City Attorney’s Office for the City of New Orleans, New Orleans, LA, for Defendants-Appellees.

Before SMITH, WIENER, and HAYNES, Circuit Judges.

*196PER CURIAM: *

Lindsey Hanson appeals the denial of a writ of execution and of sanctions. We have reviewed the briefs, pertinent portions of the record, and the applicable law and have heard the arguments of counsel. We find no reversible error. We AFFIRM the district court essentially for the reasons given by that court.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
